<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
The specific epithet 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">magnifica</emphasis>
is derived from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">magnicus</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">a</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">um</emphasis>
(a. splendid, magnificent) and is named for the magnificent, showy, vivid fuchsia-pink flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="distribution and ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schrire &amp; V. R. Clark" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera magnifica" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Indigofera magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confined to the summit plateau of the Toorberg-Koudeveld-Meelberg in the western Sneeuberg, between 1700-2150 m. The species is occasional to abundant, found exclusively on the dolerite-derived loamy-clays and black turf soils typical of this plateau. The vegetation type is Karoo Escarpment Grassland (Gh1, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mucina, L" journalOrPublisher="Strelitzia" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 807" refId="B10" refString="Mucina, L, Rutherford, MC, 2006. The Vegetation of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Strelitzia Vol. 19: 1 - 807" title="The Vegetation of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland." volume="Vol. 19" year="2006">Mucina and Rutherford 2006</bibRefCitation>
), typical of high altitudes in the Sneeuberg mountain complex, with the dominant grass species being 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N.P.Barker &amp; H.P.Linder" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Tenaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tenaxia" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Tenaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.J.Conert" authorityYear="1970" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merxmuellera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Merxmuellera" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Merxmuellera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Conert" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Nees" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merxmuellera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="disticha" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="disticha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">disticha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nees) N.P. Barker &amp; H.P. Linder. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schrire &amp; V. R. Clark" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera magnifica" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Indigofera magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is particularly abundant on the highest parts of the plateau near the eastern and southern scarps, where it forms large colonies. It compliments a suite of several local endemics only found in the western Sneeuberg, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartling &amp; H.L.Wendland" authorityYear="1824" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Acmadenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acmadenia" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Acmadenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. G. H. Oliver" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Bolus" class="Eudicots" family="Ericaceae" genus="Erica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Erica passerinoides" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="passerinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Erica passerinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bolus) E.G.H. Oliv., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="B. Nordenst" authorityYear="1961" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Euryops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euryops dentatus" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Euryops dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
B. Nord. and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rourke &amp; V. R. Clark" authorityYear="2013" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Proteaceae" genus="Faurea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Faurea recondita" order="Proteales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="recondita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Faurea recondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rourke &amp; V.R. Clark (
